HEADWORD: Maleo
<hw>Ma"le*o</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From its native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A bird of Celebes
(<spn>megacephalon maleo</spn>), allied to the brush turkey. It makes
mounds in which to lay its eggs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

